modules.description: This library supports incremental hashing operations, including initialization, updating with strings or bigarray buffers, and finalizing digests for string, buffer, file, and channel inputs. It facilitates conversion between hexadecimal and binary digest representations, along with equality checks for comparing hash values, enabling use cases like data integrity verification, cryptographic signatures, and secure data serialization.

This module supports SHA-1 hash computation and manipulation through incremental processing of data from strings, Bigarray buffers, or input channels, culminating in finalized digest values. It enables conversion between binary and hexadecimal hash representations, equality checks for digests, and secure checksum generation for files or streams. These features are particularly suited for data integrity verification, cryptographic applications, and efficient handling of large or streamed datasets.

This module enables SHA-256 hash computation with context management, data ingestion from strings, buffers, files, and channels, and digest serialization to binary or hexadecimal formats. It supports use cases like data integrity verification, secure communication, and persistent hash storage through operations that handle both incremental updates and direct digest generation, while providing safe/unsafe variants for performance-critical scenarios. The module also facilitates digest comparison and format conversions between internal, binary, and hexadecimal representations.
